{
  "text": "First, we determine (and go to) the frame of reference in which the matrix \u2206u(t) \u2206u(t) 0 is diagonal. Then, we use the time-dependent analytic expressions from [CITATION_1] to determine in this frame D 1 , D 2 , D 3 , and the rest of the selfdiffusion coefficients. Finally, we can transform D back to the original frame of reference. This procedure can be applied to particles of arbitrary shapes.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29907941"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "29907941": {
      "title": "Note: Brownian motion of colloidal particles of arbitrary shape",
      "abstract": "The analytical expressions for the time-dependent cross correlations of the translational and rotational Brownian displacements of a particle with arbitrary shape are derived. The reference center is arbitrary, and the reference frame is such that the rotational-rotational diffusion tensor is diagonal."
    }
  }
}